  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234&sectionId=47384&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Departmentalisation of Union`
  line `Accounts (Transfer of Personnel) Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day of March, 1976.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47385)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Transfer of officers and employees of the Indian Audit and Accounts Department.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234&sectionId=47385&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where the President has by order under the first proviso to sub-section (1) of section 10 of the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General's (Duties, Powers and Conditions of Service) Act, 1971 (56 of 1971),`
  line `provided for relieving, with effect from any date (hereinafter referred to as the prescribed date), the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General from the responsibility for compiling any accounts of the Union or of`
  line `any services or departments of the Union as may be specified in such order, then, subject to the provisions`
  line `of this Act, it shall be lawful for the Central Government, on the advice of a Committee established under`
  line `sub-section (2), to transfer, by order and with effect from such date or dates (which may be either`
  line `retrospective to any date not earlier than the prescribed date or prospective) as may be specified in the`
  line `order, to any Ministry or Department of the Central Government or any of its attached or subordinate`
  line `offices, any of the officers or employees serving in the Indian Audit and Accounts Department, for the`
  line `purpose of facilitating the efficient discharge by such Ministry, Department or office of the responsibility`
  line `of compiling such accounts:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made in relation to any such officer or`
  line `employee serving in the Indian Audit and Accounts Department who has, in respect of the proposal made`
  line `on the advice of the Committee to transfer such officer or employee under this sub-section, intimated,`
  line `within such time as may be specified in this behalf his unwillingness to be so transferred, unless the`
  line `Central Government is of opinion that it is necessary in the public interest to transfer such officer or`
  line `employee as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall affect the right of any such officer or employee`
  line `to resign or retire from service in accordance with the rules applicable to him in the Indian Audit and`
  line `Accounts Department.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more Advisory Committees consisting of`
  line `such number of members as it thinks fit for the purpose of assisting it in regard to the transfer of officers`
  line `and employees under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) An officer or other employee transferred to any Ministry, Department or office of the Central`
  line `Government by an order made under sub-section (1) shall, on and from the date of transfer, cease to be an`
  line `officer or employee in the Indian Audit and Accounts Department and shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (4) and of any law or rules made under Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution, hold office`
  line `in such Ministry, Department or office with such designation as the Central Government may specify.`
  line
  line `(4) Every officer or employee transferred under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to be appointed to a`
  line `post carrying a scale of pay not less favourable than that of the post which he held immediately before the`
  line `date of such transfer and in the same capacity (whether substantive or officiating) in which he held the`
  line `post last mentioned:`
  line
  line `Provided that if immediately before the date of such transfer any such officer or employee is`
  line `officiating in a higher post in the Indian Audit and Accounts Department either in a leave vacancy or in`
  line `any other vacancy of a specified duration, his pay, on transfer, shall be protected for the unexpired period`
  line `of such vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47386)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234&sectionId=47386&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_26_00001_197676_1517807318234
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Departmentalisation of Union Accounts (Transfer of Personnel)`
  line `Ordinance, 1976 (2 of 1976), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
